{"author":{"id":"7a44e6dd78392227ec436a4e10846d47c08384a2fec9ddf05df3b184b8053e38"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1760012742,"nonce":"6pL1dLDtrhzhiDuqqYghASLLF44=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOAW4Y0s7QjcZ2","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/7352","origin":"github"},"title":"EdgeR tool fails with interaction terms due to invalid column names in makeContrasts","message":"The Galaxy EdgeR tool fails when using interaction terms in the model formula because it creates design matrix column names that are not syntactically valid R names, causing makeContrasts() to fail.\n\nRoot Cause\n\nIn edger.R lines 427-430, the tool strips factor prefixes from design matrix column names but does not ensure the resulting names are syntactically valid:\n\n```\ndesign \u003c- model.matrix(formula, factors)\n\nfor (i in seq_along(factor_list)) {\n    colnames(design) \u003c- gsub(factor_list[i], \"\", colnames(design), fixed = TRUE)\n}\n```\n\nWhen interaction terms are present, model.matrix() creates column names like TreatmentA:TimePoint2, and after prefix stripping becomes A:TimePoint2, which contains a colon and is not a valid R name for makeContrasts().\n\n# Minimal Example to Reproduce\n\nInput Files:\n\ncount_matrix.txt:\n\n```\nGeneID\tSample1\tSample2\tSample3\tSample4\nGene1\t100\t150\t120\t180\nGene2\t200\t250\t220\t280\nGene3\t50\t75\t60\t90\n```\n\nfactors.txt:\n\n```\nSample\tTreatment\tTime\nSample1\tA\tT1\nSample2\tA\tT2\nSample3\tB\tT1\nSample4\tB\tT2\n```\n\ncontrasts.txt:\n\n```\nA:T2-A:T1\nB:T2-B:T1\n```\n\nFormula: `~ Treatment + Time + Treatment:Time`\n\nError:\n\n```\nError in makeContrasts(contrasts = contrast_data, levels = design) : \n  The levels must by syntactically valid names in R, see help(make.names).  Non-valid names: A:T2,B:T2\n```\n\n# Expected vs Actual Behavior\n\nExpected: The tool should either:\n\n- Create syntactically valid column names, OR\n- Handle interaction terms with backticks in contrasts\n\nActual: Tool fails because column names contain colons which are invalid in R names.\n\nProposed Solution\nAdd make.names() call after the prefix stripping:\n\n```\ndesign \u003c- model.matrix(formula, factors)\n\nfor (i in seq_along(factor_list)) {\n    colnames(design) \u003c- gsub(factor_list[i], \"\", colnames(design), fixed = TRUE)\n}\n\n# FIX: Ensure column names are syntactically valid\ncolnames(design) \u003c- make.names(colnames(design))\n```\n\nThis would convert A:T2 to A.T2, making it a valid R name that can be used in contrasts.\n\n# Impact\n\nThis bug prevents users from:\n\nTesting interaction effects between factors\nPerforming time-course experiments with treatment groups\nUsing any multi-factor design with interaction terms\nThe bug affects any analysis where biological questions involve how different groups respond differently over time or conditions.","files":null}]}